1
00:00:00,002 --> 00:01:20,002
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:02:51,376 --> 00:02:54,462
Are you okay sharing the unit
with someone else?

3
00:02:54,963 --> 00:02:57,173
Hi. I'm Lorelei Rios.

4
00:03:02,178 --> 00:03:03,428
Loki Mendez.

5
00:03:03,429 --> 00:03:06,641
What was that incident
you're running away from?

6
00:03:10,770 --> 00:03:12,606
I feel like we're gonna be BFFs.

7
00:03:18,277 --> 00:03:19,591
Here he goes again.

8
00:03:19,624 --> 00:03:21,042
I need to report this.

9
00:03:26,552 --> 00:03:28,637
Looks like I went into the wrong room.

10
00:03:28,662 --> 00:03:29,830
I believe I can help you.

11
00:03:41,133 --> 00:03:42,675
Because of some worthless guy.

12
00:03:42,676 --> 00:03:43,802
Take back what you said!

13
00:03:45,429 --> 00:03:47,640
I want you to join the Q.E.D. Club.

14
00:03:52,770 --> 00:03:53,854
Ma’am! Sir!

15
00:03:54,271 --> 00:03:55,480
You're not allowed to be here.

16
00:03:55,481 --> 00:03:56,481
Come down now.

17
00:03:57,024 --> 00:04:00,277
If anything happens to you here,
the school will be accountable.

18
00:04:13,707 --> 00:04:15,292
Does your silence mean yes?

19
00:04:17,419 --> 00:04:18,579
You're really something, huh?

20
00:04:19,046 --> 00:04:20,046
Is this a prank?

21
00:04:20,339 --> 00:04:24,468
Of all people, why did you pick me
to join your detective club?

22
00:04:25,844 --> 00:04:28,389
The Student Council
wants to shutdown Q.E.D. Club.

23
00:04:29,515 --> 00:04:31,308
They said there aren't any other members.

24
00:04:32,559 --> 00:04:34,436
My club needs to have another member

25
00:04:34,644 --> 00:04:36,646
or else, they’ll take away my club room.

26
00:04:37,398 --> 00:04:39,566
Okay, so why is that my problem?

27
00:04:39,817 --> 00:04:40,817
You're right.

28
00:04:41,652 --> 00:04:42,695
It’s not your problem.

29
00:04:43,821 --> 00:04:45,447
It’s the favor you owe me.

30
00:04:46,615 --> 00:04:48,575
In exchange for helping you with Linda.

31
00:04:49,159 --> 00:04:50,619
Her name is Lisa,

32
00:04:50,786 --> 00:04:51,914
not Linda.

33
00:04:51,954 --> 00:04:54,747
Also, of all the things you could ask me,

34
00:04:54,748 --> 00:04:55,833
why did it have to be this?

35
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:57,883
Is there nothing else?

36
00:04:57,960 --> 00:04:59,293
I mean, I don't know.

37
00:04:59,294 --> 00:05:03,674
I can run you some school errands
or get you one month free coffee.

38
00:05:03,841 --> 00:05:06,635
- Or something...
- Unless, you can give me my own club room.

39
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:09,179
I don't need those.

40
00:05:10,222 --> 00:05:13,308
The Student Council Vice President
is bullying me.

41
00:05:14,393 --> 00:05:16,060
He knows it will be hard for me

42
00:05:16,061 --> 00:05:17,520
to pursuade anyone

43
00:05:17,521 --> 00:05:18,772
to join my club.

44
00:05:19,231 --> 00:05:20,983
That's why he ordered the shutdown.

45
00:05:22,026 --> 00:05:25,236
Look, whatever your issue is
with the Student Council VP,

46
00:05:25,237 --> 00:05:26,655
that’s none of my business.

47
00:05:26,864 --> 00:05:29,866
But I can’t join the Q.E.D. Club.

48
00:05:29,867 --> 00:05:32,494
Because I don't know anything
about solving mysteries.

49
00:05:32,911 --> 00:05:34,121
I’m not meant for that.

50
00:05:35,539 --> 00:05:36,999
But you have a talent for writing.

51
00:05:37,541 --> 00:05:38,541
Right?

52
00:05:39,001 --> 00:05:40,002
You have a blog.

53
00:05:40,753 --> 00:05:41,753
Yes?

54
00:05:41,837 --> 00:05:42,837
So what?

55
00:05:43,213 --> 00:05:45,673
The Q.E.D. Club is the perfect avenue

56
00:05:45,674 --> 00:05:47,676
to showcase your journalist skills.

57
00:05:48,385 --> 00:05:49,385
Just saying.

58
00:06:01,148 --> 00:06:04,233
Today, he asked me to join his club.

59
00:06:04,234 --> 00:06:06,778
I don't even know why I
told him I owe him a favor.

60
00:06:06,803 --> 00:06:10,098
After all, he's the one
who actually wronged me.

61
00:07:29,309 --> 00:07:30,348
Loki?

62
00:07:31,871 --> 00:07:33,020
Loki?

63
00:07:48,661 --> 00:07:50,580
♪ Shadows. ♪

64
00:07:51,583 --> 00:07:54,294
♪ Creeping slowly through the dark. ♪

65
00:07:55,003 --> 00:07:59,048
♪ Watching, blocking, like. ♪

66
00:07:59,049 --> 00:08:02,594
♪ You can't even take a step. ♪

67
00:08:03,553 --> 00:08:07,139
♪ Every cry, every shake. ♪

68
00:08:07,140 --> 00:08:10,309
♪ Only walls reflect the ache. ♪

69
00:08:10,310 --> 00:08:13,270
♪ All the echoes burn inside. ♪

70
00:08:13,271 --> 00:08:17,776
♪ Like fire and bullets in the past. ♪

71
00:08:19,152 --> 00:08:21,279
♪ Listen to the warnings. ♪

72
00:08:22,531 --> 00:08:24,908
♪ Threats are drawing near. ♪

73
00:08:25,992 --> 00:08:29,663
♪ This is not the world you thought. ♪

74
00:08:30,330 --> 00:08:32,957
♪ You would know. ♪

75
00:08:32,958 --> 00:08:35,418
♪ Listen to the warnings. ♪

76
00:08:36,419 --> 00:08:38,547
♪ Open up your eyes. ♪

77
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:43,385
♪ This is not the world you thought. ♪

78
00:08:44,094 --> 00:08:46,637
♪ You would know. ♪

79
00:08:46,638 --> 00:08:51,476
♪ Listen to the warnings. ♪

80
00:08:56,269 --> 00:08:57,269
Act normal.

81
00:08:58,936 --> 00:08:59,936
Okay.

82
00:09:02,998 --> 00:09:03,998
Okay.

83
00:10:23,799 --> 00:10:24,805
Lori.

84
00:10:24,830 --> 00:10:25,372
Why?

85
00:10:25,372 --> 00:10:26,372
What's your problem?

86
00:10:26,834 --> 00:10:27,877
What...

87
00:10:28,307 --> 00:10:29,352
Sorry, Tita.

88
00:10:29,377 --> 00:10:32,003
- What, do you think I'm a ghost?
- No, Tita. I’m sorry.

89
00:10:32,546 --> 00:10:34,671
I just get startled easily, that's all.

90
00:10:35,215 --> 00:10:36,466
How was your sleep?

91
00:10:37,426 --> 00:10:39,177
You might be lacking rest.

92
00:10:39,766 --> 00:10:41,642
That's why you're jumpy.

93
00:10:42,097 --> 00:10:44,391
You know how staying up late
messes with you, kids.

94
00:10:45,183 --> 00:10:46,393
Acutally, Tita...

95
00:10:46,977 --> 00:10:48,978
I feel kinda uncomfortable here.

96
00:10:48,979 --> 00:10:51,106
That’s why I can’t fall asleep right away.

97
00:10:51,648 --> 00:10:54,316
Do you want me to change
your mattress or pillow?

98
00:10:54,317 --> 00:10:55,609
Oh, no need.

99
00:10:55,610 --> 00:10:57,487
My pillow and bed are fine.

100
00:10:58,655 --> 00:11:00,240
It’s just...

101
00:11:00,699 --> 00:11:04,744
I think I hear rustling
in the ceiling and walls.

102
00:11:05,078 --> 00:11:06,746
That’s why I can’t fall asleep.

103
00:11:07,330 --> 00:11:11,084
But maybe it’s just my imagination,
so don’t mind me.

104
00:11:12,017 --> 00:11:16,355
I'm not trying to make you more scared,
but I just want to tell you that…

105
00:11:17,933 --> 00:11:20,184
I hear noises at night, too.

106
00:11:20,209 --> 00:11:21,209
Huh?

107
00:11:21,353 --> 00:11:22,979
Really, Tita?

108
00:11:23,105 --> 00:11:25,065
So it's not just my imagination?

109
00:11:26,108 --> 00:11:28,568
That’s what the other tenants told me too.

110
00:11:29,361 --> 00:11:30,779
What can I do?

111
00:11:31,113 --> 00:11:33,782
I don't know how to deal with spirits.

112
00:11:34,741 --> 00:11:36,493
This place's already been blessed.

113
00:11:36,573 --> 00:11:39,159
Three times already.
But it’s still the same.

114
00:11:42,074 --> 00:11:43,659
Maybe that’s the reason

115
00:11:44,419 --> 00:11:46,213
why no one stays long

116
00:11:46,589 --> 00:11:49,175
in your unit with Loki.

117
00:11:50,296 --> 00:11:53,382
They say the loudest creaks
are in your unit.

118
00:11:54,533 --> 00:11:55,784
But don't worry,

119
00:11:56,858 --> 00:12:00,987
because I always include all
my tenants in my prayers.

120
00:12:02,185 --> 00:12:03,372
That’s why I’m sure,

121
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:05,147
it's just creaks, that's all.

122
00:12:06,189 --> 00:12:07,189
Because

123
00:12:07,649 --> 00:12:10,694
you’re all protected by my prayers.

124
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:14,488
Oh, Tita, I have to go now.

125
00:12:14,489 --> 00:12:16,366
I'm sorry. Bye!

126
00:12:32,132 --> 00:12:35,093
What if bad luck is actually chasing me?

127
00:12:36,136 --> 00:12:39,347
Or worse, what if I’m the bad luck?

128
00:12:40,640 --> 00:12:43,018
It's like every world I step into...

129
00:12:43,852 --> 00:12:45,520
I end up messing things up.

130
00:12:47,189 --> 00:12:48,940
When will this ever end?

131
00:12:51,151 --> 00:12:53,487
I can't believe
I'm entering this room again.

132
00:12:54,696 --> 00:12:59,367
The same room that witnessed
how Aaron stalked me.

133
00:12:59,910 --> 00:13:03,622
I’m new here,
and I’m already in trouble again.

134
00:13:22,432 --> 00:13:23,891
Okay, guys. Settle down.

135
00:13:23,892 --> 00:13:25,185
Go back to your seats.

136
00:13:27,103 --> 00:13:29,564
It's only been a few weeks
this semester, guys,

137
00:13:30,273 --> 00:13:31,733
but we already have a lot of issues.

138
00:13:32,901 --> 00:13:34,444
Put yourselves together, huh?

139
00:13:35,278 --> 00:13:37,614
Focus on your studies.

140
00:13:38,073 --> 00:13:39,633
Not just on things that stress you out.

141
00:13:40,742 --> 00:13:42,244
Yes, sir.

142
00:13:43,453 --> 00:13:44,453
Attendance call.

143
00:13:45,413 --> 00:13:46,539
Byron, Kelvin?

144
00:13:46,540 --> 00:13:47,541
Present, sir!

145
00:13:47,874 --> 00:13:50,085
- Dela Cruz, John Paul?
- Present!

146
00:13:50,544 --> 00:13:51,753
Flores, Aaron?

147
00:13:54,548 --> 00:13:55,632
Sorry, I forgot.

148
00:13:56,466 --> 00:13:58,635
- Galang, Mary Jane?
- Present, sir!

149
00:13:59,427 --> 00:14:00,887
Jocson, Lisa Claire?

150
00:14:01,137 --> 00:14:04,015
Sir, she’s absent today
because of yesterday’s incident.

151
00:14:05,016 --> 00:14:06,226
Roque, Aina?

152
00:14:06,643 --> 00:14:07,643
Present!

153
00:14:07,686 --> 00:14:10,187
- Reyes, Von Andy?
- Present.

154
00:14:14,317 --> 00:14:18,697
Girl, just a reminder,
the org application deadline's on Friday.

155
00:14:18,863 --> 00:14:19,990
You have to decide.

156
00:14:20,365 --> 00:14:22,492
Is it really mandatory to join the org?

157
00:14:22,701 --> 00:14:24,118
Of course!

158
00:14:24,119 --> 00:14:26,579
What else are you gonna do here,
just study?

159
00:14:26,580 --> 00:14:27,956
That'd be so boring.

160
00:14:28,498 --> 00:14:33,628
And didn't the dean say
orgs cover 30 percent of our grade?

161
00:14:33,962 --> 00:14:35,797
That'd be such a waste if it happens.

162
00:14:36,798 --> 00:14:37,798
Okay, fine.

163
00:14:38,258 --> 00:14:41,386
But I was hoping for something more chill.

164
00:14:42,387 --> 00:14:43,096
How about you?

165
00:14:43,263 --> 00:14:44,514
What org did you join?

166
00:14:45,307 --> 00:14:46,933
Oh, I'm switching clubs.

167
00:14:47,183 --> 00:14:49,518
I didn’t like the club I joined last year.

168
00:14:49,519 --> 00:14:50,687
Why?

169
00:14:51,479 --> 00:14:53,606
There’s no thrill, Gardening Club.

170
00:14:53,607 --> 00:14:56,900
Like, I don’t know
if it’s just me or what.

171
00:14:56,901 --> 00:14:59,320
But it feels like
they're training me to be old.

172
00:14:59,321 --> 00:15:03,824
I'm still young.
Why turn me into a plantita at this age?

173
00:15:03,825 --> 00:15:06,243
So I feel like it has a
purpose and everything.

174
00:15:06,244 --> 00:15:08,120
But going to class?

175
00:15:08,121 --> 00:15:09,872
I want something with thrill,

176
00:15:09,873 --> 00:15:12,041
something that excites me
when I go to school.

177
00:15:12,042 --> 00:15:13,376
Something that will hype me up.

178
00:15:13,710 --> 00:15:17,422
You know, we can join
the Paranormal Club together...

179
00:15:21,885 --> 00:15:24,304
Sure, Rosetta.
Let's join the Paranormal Club.

180
00:15:24,554 --> 00:15:26,764
Yeah, Lori. That'd be fun, right?

181
00:15:26,765 --> 00:15:29,183
Especially if we're together
and there's a thrill.

182
00:15:29,184 --> 00:15:30,518
Perfect. Right?

183
00:15:31,102 --> 00:15:34,141
Yeah! I'm in. I'll hand in my application.
We can go together!

184
00:15:42,697 --> 00:15:43,632
Sorry!

185
00:15:43,657 --> 00:15:45,116
No. It’s okay.

186
00:15:45,715 --> 00:15:47,424
- I’m new here.
- Oh, okay.

187
00:15:47,449 --> 00:15:49,993
I’m just looking
for Foreign Affairs Office.

188
00:15:50,018 --> 00:15:51,230
Oh, okay.

189
00:15:51,390 --> 00:15:52,759
Well, I’m also new here.

190
00:15:53,083 --> 00:15:56,619
But I think it might be
in the other building.

191
00:15:57,545 --> 00:15:58,629
Oh, thank you so much.

192
00:15:58,630 --> 00:15:59,547
Oh, okay. Yeah.

193
00:15:59,548 --> 00:16:01,814
- Well, I see you around. No problem.
- Yeah. See you!

194
00:16:08,378 --> 00:16:11,186
Hi. Join our club, okay?

195
00:16:15,420 --> 00:16:17,713
Hi. Maybe you'd like some of our flowers?

196
00:16:17,738 --> 00:16:19,405
Maybe you want tomato???

197
00:16:19,430 --> 00:16:20,640
There are more here.

198
00:16:21,361 --> 00:16:22,538
Come, join!

199
00:16:23,003 --> 00:16:25,254
Hi. Join the Cyber Club.

200
00:16:25,279 --> 00:16:26,989
Please join the Cyber Club!

201
00:16:34,040 --> 00:16:35,040
Clarion?

202
00:16:36,376 --> 00:16:38,670
Okay, I'll think about it. I have to go.

203
00:16:43,591 --> 00:16:44,591
Okay.

204
00:16:45,176 --> 00:16:46,969
Young Traveler's Club.

205
00:16:46,970 --> 00:16:50,264
- Lori! Why did you leave me at the locker?
- Rosetta.

206
00:16:50,265 --> 00:16:52,182
Sorry. I thought you were following me.

207
00:16:52,183 --> 00:16:55,437
Come on. Let's join here. Let's go!

208
00:16:55,645 --> 00:16:56,854
There are many demons here.

209
00:16:56,855 --> 00:16:59,357
Come on! Let's go inside!

210
00:16:59,941 --> 00:17:00,941
Hi!

211
00:17:04,988 --> 00:17:07,281
- Look.
- What's this?

212
00:17:07,531 --> 00:17:09,032
Paranormal Club!

213
00:17:18,334 --> 00:17:21,086
Come on. Let’s join this.

214
00:17:21,087 --> 00:17:22,671
Hold on. It's just...

215
00:17:22,672 --> 00:17:25,717
I’m not sure yet.
Besides, I don’t have a third eye.

216
00:17:26,176 --> 00:17:29,763
Even with just two eyes, it's fine.
You can still join our club.

217
00:17:31,556 --> 00:17:33,849
That's right. Stay here. It’s fun here.

218
00:17:33,850 --> 00:17:36,518
Yeah, this is very thrilling.

219
00:17:36,519 --> 00:17:38,729
They've got ghost-hunting activities.

220
00:17:38,730 --> 00:17:41,107
Come on, let's join.

221
00:18:13,515 --> 00:18:15,183
Can you be more careful with that?

222
00:18:15,558 --> 00:18:17,477
What if that hit me?

223
00:18:17,769 --> 00:18:18,769
Why?

224
00:18:18,978 --> 00:18:19,978
Did it hit you?

225
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:21,480
It didn’t, right?

226
00:18:21,898 --> 00:18:23,024
You’re not my target.

227
00:18:23,775 --> 00:18:24,775
Whatever!

228
00:18:24,984 --> 00:18:25,985
As expected...

229
00:18:27,028 --> 00:18:28,696
you won’t see me in the club room.

230
00:18:29,531 --> 00:18:30,865
And you'll still go home early.

231
00:18:32,367 --> 00:18:33,367
No way.

232
00:18:33,910 --> 00:18:35,662
I just really want to rest.

233
00:18:36,204 --> 00:18:37,204
Why?

234
00:18:37,580 --> 00:18:38,665
Maybe you're wondering.

235
00:18:39,207 --> 00:18:40,917
I transferred my work place here.

236
00:18:41,876 --> 00:18:44,076
Since they're kicking me out
of the club room very soon.

237
00:18:44,295 --> 00:18:46,172
I need to try to find a new place

238
00:18:46,631 --> 00:18:47,882
where I can continue my work.

239
00:18:48,383 --> 00:18:49,425
Thanks to you.

240
00:18:51,511 --> 00:18:52,512
Are you mad?

241
00:18:53,137 --> 00:18:54,137
Is that why...

242
00:18:54,597 --> 00:18:58,101
you're picking
on the photo of that innocent guy?

243
00:19:03,147 --> 00:19:04,147
Nope.

244
00:19:04,440 --> 00:19:06,484
The word "innocent" doesn't suit him.

245
00:19:07,569 --> 00:19:09,904
He’s anything but innocent!

246
00:19:11,030 --> 00:19:13,116
The word "despicable" suits him better.

247
00:19:13,783 --> 00:19:16,286
If you run into this person
in the hallway,

248
00:19:17,537 --> 00:19:18,830
you better hide.

249
00:19:25,587 --> 00:19:26,629
I'm tired.

250
00:19:27,297 --> 00:19:28,586
I'm going to sleep.

251
00:19:29,143 --> 00:19:30,143
Later.

252
00:19:45,846 --> 00:19:47,473
My club needs to have another member.

253
00:19:47,854 --> 00:19:50,024
Or else, they’ll take away my club room.

254
00:20:50,713 --> 00:20:52,422
A true journalist

255
00:20:52,423 --> 00:20:55,050
is someone who does not just report

256
00:20:55,051 --> 00:20:57,220
but exposes the truth.

257
00:20:57,845 --> 00:21:02,850
The truth about what
affects us, the public.

258
00:21:03,434 --> 00:21:06,521
Unfortunately, the exposition isn’t enough.

259
00:21:06,980 --> 00:21:09,147
Things need to be well-researched,

260
00:21:09,148 --> 00:21:10,524
investigated

261
00:21:10,525 --> 00:21:11,818
and in all angles.

262
00:21:12,443 --> 00:21:14,696
This is my dream for all of you.

263
00:21:16,030 --> 00:21:19,909
You are the next generation
of storytellers

264
00:21:20,451 --> 00:21:22,703
who are committed to the truth

265
00:21:22,704 --> 00:21:25,747
and it is backed up by facts.

266
00:21:25,748 --> 00:21:27,417
So for your activity,

267
00:21:27,667 --> 00:21:29,252
let us put into action

268
00:21:29,502 --> 00:21:32,422
everything we discussed about research.

269
00:21:33,047 --> 00:21:34,882
Think of a story

270
00:21:35,508 --> 00:21:38,052
that piques your interest.

271
00:21:38,553 --> 00:21:41,431
And of course,
when you submit and present it,

272
00:21:42,140 --> 00:21:45,601
make sure it's backed up by research.

273
00:21:45,852 --> 00:21:46,477
Ma’am!

274
00:21:46,644 --> 00:21:48,229
What type of topic?

275
00:21:48,396 --> 00:21:49,396
Anything!

276
00:21:50,148 --> 00:21:52,608
Something that sparks your curiosity.

277
00:21:52,900 --> 00:21:53,609
Understood?

278
00:21:53,860 --> 00:21:55,485
Yes, ma'am.

279
00:21:55,486 --> 00:21:57,155
All right. Now, go to your groups.

280
00:21:59,198 --> 00:22:02,159
What if we make
the emergence of AI our topic instead?

281
00:22:02,160 --> 00:22:04,953
If it’s okay to use in school or at work.

282
00:22:04,954 --> 00:22:06,998
Advantages and disadvantages.

283
00:22:07,123 --> 00:22:08,249
Yeah, right.

284
00:22:09,375 --> 00:22:12,837
But I heard the other group
is also doing AI.

285
00:22:13,296 --> 00:22:15,173
What about you, girl? What do you think?

286
00:22:15,715 --> 00:22:19,093
Seriously? What if we think of a new topic?

287
00:22:19,552 --> 00:22:20,802
How about you, Lori?

288
00:22:20,803 --> 00:22:24,265
Do you have any topic in mind
that the other groups haven’t thought of?

289
00:22:25,475 --> 00:22:26,475
Hmm...

290
00:22:28,102 --> 00:22:29,102
What if..

291
00:22:29,771 --> 00:22:31,105
Mental health?

292
00:22:31,856 --> 00:22:35,068
Right? It’s relevant, after all.

293
00:22:35,276 --> 00:22:37,152
Especially after all the incidents.

294
00:22:37,153 --> 00:22:38,738
For example, what happened with Lisa.

295
00:22:39,697 --> 00:22:41,657
Maybe we can focus on..

296
00:22:41,991 --> 00:22:43,200
What are the usual signs

297
00:22:43,201 --> 00:22:45,787
that a person struggling
with his or her mental health?

298
00:22:46,496 --> 00:22:49,957
Basically, the importance
of this research is to inform

299
00:22:50,208 --> 00:22:52,460
and to give awareness to everyone.

300
00:22:53,252 --> 00:22:56,506
So that if they have loved ones

301
00:22:56,881 --> 00:22:58,007
who are struggling,

302
00:22:58,716 --> 00:23:00,052
they’ll know how to handle it.

303
00:23:04,514 --> 00:23:07,557
I feel like we’ve got our topic. Perfect!

304
00:23:07,558 --> 00:23:09,060
I know right, girl!

305
00:23:09,435 --> 00:23:11,311
Yeah. Let’s go with that one.

306
00:23:11,312 --> 00:23:12,312
Nice one!

307
00:23:13,564 --> 00:23:15,107
Sounds good. Let's go?

308
00:23:15,108 --> 00:23:16,109
- Let’s start?
- Yeah.

309
00:23:18,486 --> 00:23:19,612
Alright.

310
00:23:25,576 --> 00:23:26,618
That’s Lori!

311
00:23:26,619 --> 00:23:28,703
- Yeah, you’re right!
- Come on! Let’s go to Lori!

312
00:23:28,704 --> 00:23:29,704
Excuse me!

313
00:23:32,083 --> 00:23:33,084
Lori!

314
00:23:33,417 --> 00:23:34,168
Hey!

315
00:23:34,293 --> 00:23:35,627
Why are you eating by yourself?

316
00:23:35,628 --> 00:23:37,672
- I thought we were having lunch together.
- Hi, Lori!

317
00:23:38,005 --> 00:23:38,881
Sorry!

318
00:23:38,882 --> 00:23:40,466
I got hungry.

319
00:23:40,716 --> 00:23:42,093
We’ll join you.

320
00:23:43,803 --> 00:23:45,972
So, have you chosen a club to join?

321
00:23:46,472 --> 00:23:48,057
I haven’t decided yet.

322
00:23:48,599 --> 00:23:50,768
Since you’re still having
a hard time deciding,

323
00:23:51,102 --> 00:23:53,186
come join me
in the Paranormal Club for now.

324
00:23:53,187 --> 00:23:54,396
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

325
00:23:54,397 --> 00:23:56,523
- Come on, join us.
- Yeah, Lori.

326
00:23:56,524 --> 00:23:57,524
It's fun.

327
